headline.main: WAR IN KANSAS.; True Version of the Affair at Franklin Attack on the Pro-Stavery Group at Washington Creek. RESCUE OF GOV. ROBINSON. LECOMPTON TAKEN BY THE FREE-STATE MEN. News by Mail. SAFETY OF LANES PARTY--PRO-SLAVERY CAMP BROKEN UP NEAR OSSAWATOMIE, ETC. Late and Highly Important by Telegraph. GOV. ROBINSON RESCUED--LECOMPTON TAKEN BY THE FREE-STATE MEN. RUMORED ATTACK ON SOUTHERNERS--TRUE VERSION OF THE FRANKLIN AFFAIR.

docs.lead_paragraph: LANES party are all safe and will be in ?? ka Wednesday night. They have met no opposition--have seen no Missourians or soldiers,--have built a good road all the way--are in good health and spirits--well provided with teams and farming utensils--have located two towns on the way on pleasant sites, and left a part of the men to settle them.
